Author::::philemondaba
DateTime::::2016-03-06T11:34:49Z
I never claimed any moral superiority, nor did I use the words "non-racist". I left my country because of the modern horrors. The horrors of female friends and family being raped, your Grandparents being murdered on the farm and the constant immovable fear that your life is in mortal danger. Perhaps Apartheid had horrors, perhaps not. I don't really care. I didn't perpertrate any, nor did my family, nor anyone I know. I won't accept your notions of transferable guilt or "privilege". I know and knew my own horrific realities and I hold views on how to improve the lot for all of us, not just my own people, because I care deeply for Africa. You are free to self-flagellate and accept your and everybody else's culture, history and dignity being vilified and denigrated on the back of a failed, internationalist dogma, but I won't stand for it, and as you know, neither will most of my peers. I travel home often enough to know this to be true.



