Author::::philemondaba
DateTime::::2016-03-06T08:06:37Z
As a white South Africa living in Europe, I find it disingenuous for the few white South Africans on the left, both Anglos and Afrikaners, to insist that we are part of Africa but somehow not part of its problems or shortcomings. Instead, we are a pastiche of neo-liberal, self-flagellating thought, straight out of Europe or America. Allow me to weigh in with some fact - we are not Europeans nor Americans. We do not think the same way, nor do we or should we subscribe to the same defeatest and masochistic laws and mores that they subject themselves to. We are African, yes. And with that comes all the tribalism and macho-superiority that is the blight of the continent. We cannot escape it by spouting platitudes and using imported reasoning. South Africans, white, black, coloured and indian are tribalists, not racists. And we are this way by virtue of our cultures, histories and circumstances. The only way to solve our problems is for ethnic self determination of each group within sub-saharan Africa. Not just the Afrikaners, Anglo-Africans, Xhosas or Zulus in South Africa, but also the other groups forced together through colonialism - the Matabele and the Shona in Zimbabwe for example. Only once we have achieved this, will we have peace. This is an African problem that requires African solutions, not limp social democratic European inanity.



